    "children": [
      {
        "type": "email",
        "html": "<p>Hey {first_name, \"there\"},</p><p>Day 2 of the new regime. Still here. Still enjoying it. I hope you're finding it valuable, too.&nbsp;</p><p>I even have a schedule for the rest of the week:&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Wednesday: How Substack and cancel culture are birthing a new media</li><li>Thursday: Social &amp; Digital coffee break (links round-up)</li><li>Friday: What the debate about Apple News+ is missing</li></ul><p>Onwards to today's links…</p>"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Social Media's difficult teenage years",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "koenig-heading",
        "tag": "h2",
        "version": 1,
        "renderVersion": "3.0"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Social media has long been the glamorous part of audience engagement work (from the outside, at least), compared to the technical detail of SEO, and the slow, steady work of building newsletters. Indeed, up until a couple of years ago, social media and audience engagement were largely synonymous. Thankfully, that is changing quickly. ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Reducing your dependence on social as an acquisition channel feels vital now, as the social media waters feel more choppy than I can ever recall them being in the 20-odd years I've been tracking this stuff. ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "On the one hand, you have Facebook looking ever-so-slightly desperate in its moves to maintain and protect its position. Instagram seems to be the main \"beneficiary\" of its efforts, with some fundamental changes, from the advent of TikTok clone Reels, and also a shift in the algorithm, ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "to give you more “discovery” content",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "link",
            "rel": null,
            "target": null,
            "title": null,
            "url": "https://www.forbes.com/sites/abrambrown/2020/08/19/instagram-reaches-for-more-of-tiktoks-magic-with-a-change-to-its-main-feed/",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": ". A simplistic reading of that change would be that Instagram is, in effect, merging your feed and the discover tab to make room for Reels…",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "The move has not been well-received in some quarters, as this thread makes clear:",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "bookmark",
        "url": "https://threadreaderapp.com/thread/1302978610303770627.html",
        "metadata": {
